value.name: Gallup: 63% of Americans Dissatisfied With Immigration
value.snippet: Font Size. (Getty Images) (CNSNews.com) -- A new poll shows that 63% of American adults are dissatisfied with immigration and that among that percentage, 40% want immigration decreased. By the same token, 15% are dissatisfied and want immigration to stay the same while 8% are dissatisfied but want it to increase.

value.name: Gallup: 63% of American Adults Drink Alcohol, Beer is Favorite
value.snippet: However, among adults making $40,000 to $99,999 a year, only 63% said they drink alcohol. (Gallup) For those making less than a $40,000 a year, only 49% said they drink. Among the educated, 75% of adults with a post-graduate degree drink; 76% of adults with a college degree only; 65% with some college; and only 51% with no college.

value.name: Gallup: 63% of Americans Dissatisfied With Immigration
value.snippet: For those 55 and older who are dissatisfied with immigration, the percentage has risen from 21% in 2021 to 55% today. “Over the same period, it has also increased a sizable amount among middle-aged adults, aged 35 to 54, rising from 23% to 40%, while showing little change among younger adults,” reported Gallup.
